Peru Stocks: Austral, Ferreyros, Relapasa, Siderperu, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-08T20:57:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/peru-stocks-austral-ferreyros-maple-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a seventh session, plunging
7.1 percent to 18,730.56. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
declined 6 percent to 2,365.19.  Industrial stocks slumped after  Standard & Poor’s 
downgraded the U.S. credit rating, said Javier Frisancho, a
trader at Lima-based brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA known as Relapasa, plummeted 11 percent to 76
centimos after crude futures declined in New York.  Empresa
Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), the Gerdau SA unit known
as Siderperu, fell 10 percent to 1.21 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
dropped 10 percent to 2.30 soles. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA
(CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, declined 10 percent to
2.21 soles. Austral Group SA (AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll
Seafood ASA, fell 9.1 percent to 30 centimos.  Mining stocks dropped after metals declined in New York and
 London .  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc
exploration company, fell 11 percent to 16 cents. Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc and silver mining
company, declined 9.5 percent to 95 centimos.  Candente Copper
Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, dropped 9.2
percent to $1.09. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s
largest zinc producer, slid 9.1 percent to 2.70 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, fell 9
percent to 3.05 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  